# Vercel Web Analytics Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the beskydy-soaring-weather Next.js project following the latest official documentation.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **Installed:** `@vercel/analytics` version `^2.0.1`
- **Package Manager:** npm (as detected from existing `package-lock.json`)
- **Installation Command:** `npm install @vercel/analytics`

### 2. Code Changes
**Modified:** `app/layout.tsx`

Added the Analytics component following Next.js App Router best practices:
- Imported `Analytics` from `@vercel/analytics/next`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag in the RootLayout component

This implementation follows the official Vercel documentation retrieved from:
https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart

### 3. Files Updated
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency and its sub-dependencies

## Implementation Details

The Analytics component was added to the root layout following the framework-specific instructions for Next.js App Router:
1. Imported the Analytics component from `@vercel/analytics/next`
2. Placed the component inside the body tag, after the children content
3. Preserved all existing code structure and formatting

## Verification Steps Completed

✅ **Build Test:** Successfully ran `npm run build` - project builds without errors
✅ **Linting:** Ran `npm run lint` on modified file - no new linting errors introduced
✅ **Dependencies:** Lock file (`package-lock.json`) properly updated with 371 new packages

## Notes

- The Analytics component will only collect data when the app is deployed to Vercel
- Web Analytics must be enabled in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics section) for data collection
- In development mode, the component is present but won't send tracking data
- Pre-existing linting errors in `components/WeatherChart.tsx` were not addressed as they are unrelated to this change

## Next Steps for Deployment

1. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard
3. Verify tracking is working by checking the browser Network tab for requests to `/<unique-path>/view`
4. Monitor analytics data in the Vercel dashboard

## Package Details

The `@vercel/analytics` package provides:
- Zero-config analytics for Vercel deployments
- Privacy-friendly tracking (no cookies)
- Real-time visitor insights
- Lightweight client-side tracking script
